      <preamble>
         <p>The Scottish Ministers make the following Order in exercise of the powers conferred by section 6A(1)(aa) and (1B) of the Valuation and Rating (Scotland) Act 1956<noteRef href="#f00001" class="footnote" marker="1"/> and all other powers enabling them to do so.</p>
         <formula name="enactingText">
            <p>In accordance with section 6A(1D) that Act<noteRef href="#f00002" class="footnote" marker="2"/> they have consulted such associations of local authorities and such other persons as they think appropriate.</p>
         </formula>
      </preamble>
      <body>
         <article eId="article-1">
            <heading>Citation and commencement</heading>
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
               <p>This Order may be cited as the Non-Domestic Rating (Valuation of Utilities) (Scotland) Amendment (No. 2) Order 2019 and comes into force on 31 March 2019.</p>
            </content>
         </article>
         <article eId="article-2">
            <heading>Amendment of the Non-Domestic Rating (Valuation of Utilities) (Scotland) Amendment Order 2019</heading>
            <num>2.</num>
            <paragraph eId="article-2-1">
               <num>(1)</num>
               <content>
                  <p>The Non-Domestic Rating (Valuation of Utilities) (Scotland) Amendment Order 2019<noteRef href="#f00003" class="footnote" marker="3"/> is amended as follows.</p>
               </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="article-2-2">
               <num>(2)</num>
               <intro>
                  <p>In the table in article 6 (company names and registration numbers for fixed line telecommunications operators)—</p>
               </intro>
               <subparagraph eId="article-2-2-a">
                  <num>(a)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>in the entry for “Centurylink Communications <abbr class="acronym" title="United Kingdom">UK</abbr> Limited”, for the registration number substitute “02495998”,</p>
                  </content>
               </subparagraph>
               <subparagraph eId="article-2-2-b">
                  <num>(b)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>omit the entry for “Orange Limited” and the corresponding registration number,</p>
                  </content>
               </subparagraph>
               <subparagraph eId="article-2-2-c">
                  <num>(c)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>omit the entry for “Pipex Broadband Limited” and the corresponding registration number,</p>
                  </content>
               </subparagraph>
               <subparagraph eId="article-2-2-d">
                  <num>(d)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>for “Sky Telecommunications Services Ltd” substitute “Sky Telecommunications Services Limited”, and</p>
                  </content>
               </subparagraph>
               <subparagraph eId="article-2-2-e">
                  <num>(e)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>for “Talk Talk Communications Ltd” substitute “Talktalk Communications Limited”.</p>
                  </content>
               </subparagraph>
            </paragraph>
         </article>
